Description: 
Steven Hydes was abandoned in a women's toilet at 
Gatwick Airport when he was just ten days old. Now 24, 
and having been brought up by a loving adopted family, 
the remarkably magnanimous Steven is understandably 
curious to find out who his birth mother is and the details 
of the first days of his life. This quietly emotional film
 follows Steven as he returns to Gatwick to meet the 
airport workers who found him, talks to the police officer in 
charge of investigating his case, and takes a fascinating 
DNA test to pinpoint where in the world his ancestry lies.
